This paper is about attention models in natural language processing, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the interaction between computers and human language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, attention models are a type of machine learning algorithm, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of attention in neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of attention in computer vision, which is a related field and falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
